[normal]1.[bold]              [bold]Introduction[bold].[bold]1.1
[normal]              
[normal]Natural England is the 
[normal]Government’s statutory advis
[normal]e
[normal]r on the natural environment. Natural England’s purpose is to ensure that the natural environment is conserved, enhanced and managed for the benefit of present and future generations, thereby contributing to sustainable develop
[normal]ment.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2
[normal]              
[normal]Natural England is responsible for delivering, on behalf of the 
[normal]Department for the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs
[normal] (Defra),
[normal] 
[normal]Environmental Stewardship 
[normal]and other 
[normal]schemes which offer payments to farmers and 
[normal]other 
[normal]land m
[normal]anagers in England for un
[normal]dertaking
[normal] land management
[normal] practices
[normal],
[normal] which
[normal] go beyond 
[normal]minimal regulatory compliance
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]to protect and enhance the environment and wildlife. These schemes form part of the 
[normal]current 
[normal]Rural Development Programme for England (RDPE) (2007-20
[normal]13
[normal]).
[normal] Natural England 
[normal]delivers 
[normal]over 51,000 agri-environment agre
[normal]e
[normal]ments, covering about 70% of English agricultural land, which provide over £400m support 
[normal]each year 
[normal]for 
[normal]environmental
[normal] land management
[normal] by farmers and land managers
[normal].
[normal]  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.3
[normal]              
[normal]Natural England is 
[normal]also 
[normal]Defra’s largest del
[normal]iverer of on-farm advice
[normal].
[normal] Our advisers deliver around 
[normal]13,000 farm visits each year
[normal] 
[normal]advising on a range of environmental, ecological, agronomic and management issues,
[normal] specialising
[normal] in helping farmers access funding streams for environmental land management and assessing the outcomes they deliver. We deliver our advice through face to face visits; to groups; through farm walks, demonstrations, farmer meetings and conferences. In addi
[normal]tion, we provide telephone support and on line services to farmers to support their delivery of our agri-environment
[normal] programmes
[normal].
[normal] 
